study.description: Develop an assay against a defined target, role out in production and screen the compound library creating a 'hit' list.
study.name: HTS Program

study-parameter.description: support reader counts such as CPM (counts per minute) and DPM (disintegrations per minute)
study-parameter.name: Counts

study-parameter.description: In as a place holder until we can link to the study data element
study-parameter.name: Assay Definition

study-parameter.description: Summary statistic for fits ie XC50, IC50, EC50
study-parameter.name: XC50

study-parameter.description: Fir statistics such as hill, r2 etc
study-parameter.name: Fit Statistic

study-parameter.description: Plate control values mean pos, neg etc
study-parameter.name: Control

study-parameter.description: pass or fail plate or curve
study-parameter.name: QC

study-parameter.description: Hit threshold, can be altered at plate level
study-parameter.name: Hit Threshold

study-parameter.description: The compound of interest. This is an abstract concept and would really require linking to the supporting inventory, ie batches, lots, samples, vials and plates
study-parameter.name: Compound

study-parameter.description: The biological target against which the screen will be developed. This would be linked into an external system no doubt.
study-parameter.name: Target

study-parameter.description: Generic text field for non-dictionary identifiers.
study-parameter.name: Label

study-parameter.description: Used to define positional/co-ordinate information for plates and other inventory.
study-parameter.name: Position

study-queue.description: Develop an assay against the validated target. Inputs are the target id, the outputs are the study definition and an SOP.
study-queue.name: Develop Assay

study-queue.description: Submit a list of compounds for a dose response assay. This service is for informal requests for medicinal chemists who are re-iterating compound libraries based on SAR analysis
study-queue.name: Fit curves

study-protocol.description: A single point screen. Inputs are the compound library against the new assay (and therefore target), the output is a list of 'hits' which will be confirmed.
study-protocol.name: Primary Screen

study-protocol.description: Confirm hits from primary screen. Input are actives from primary screen, outputs are actives that agree within 3 standard deviations. Confirmation is carried out in duplicate.
study-protocol.name: Secondary Screen

study-protocol.description: Take confirmed hits from secondary screen and process through an 8 point dose response to identify either IC50 or max % Inhibition.
study-protocol.name: Dose Response

study-protocol.description: Implement a new assay against the submitted target. There are a number of outputs for this process, an SOP linked to a study design which includes a collection of protocols used to capture data. Assay development start point is acceptance of the validated target. The end point is the implementation of the study design.
study-protocol.name: Assay Development
